title: Icehouse - Sidewalk
description: Sidewalk is the third album by Australian rock synthpop band Icehouse. It was released in June 1984 on Regular Records / Chrysalis Records and reached #8 on the National albums chart with singles "Taking the Town" (#22 in May), "Don't Believe Anymore" (#22 August) and "Dusty Pages" (#82 November).[3] Founding member Iva Davies used the Fairlight CMI on this more sombre and reflective album,[4] included are two tracks used for the Russell Mulcahy 1984 film Razorback, which he had recorded in 1983.[
